oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Songwriter Session - Kent Blazy and Cory Batten - 2009-06-20
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Performance by Kent Blazy and Cory Batten from the Ford Theater at the Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum on June 20, 2009. Special appearance by Karyn Rochelle.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Kent Blazy; Cory Batten; Karyn Rochelle;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Performances include: Why Ain't I Running; Let Me Love You Right; Somewhere Other Than The Night; unidentified song, [possibly We Always Played For The Girls]; intro of Karyn Rochelle; I Hate Women I Hate Men (Corey Batten and Karyn Rochelle); Red High Heels (Karyn Rochelle); Never Knew My Dad (Kent Blazy); If You Had Called Yesterday (Cory Batten); Ain't Going Down (Til The Suns Comes Up); She Wouldn't Be Gone;
